PraxisBase includes implementation ideas adapted from:

Source-level borrowings (MIT, same language, copyright preserved):

- llm-wiki-compiler (MIT License), especially the static wiki lint and health-score
  pattern under `.local-references/llm-wiki-compiler/src/linter` and `src/eval`.
  PraxisBase's M27 provenance audit keeps the same static, no-LLM linting
  discipline while using original TypeScript code for PraxisBase's kb/skill
  provenance model.

Design-level references (ideas reimplemented in TypeScript, no code copied):

- Tencent/WeKnora (MIT License, Go). Its Wiki Mode (v0.5.0) — agents distilling
  raw input into a self-maintaining, interlinked markdown knowledge base with an
  interactive knowledge graph — overlaps most with PraxisBase's kb/ stable
  knowledge and graph page. WeKnora's interactive force-directed graph (node
  click-through, per-kind coloring), Wiki browser tree navigation, multi-source
  connector abstraction (Feishu/Notion/RSS incremental sync), and Langfuse-style
  full-chain trace spans are design references for the graph page evolution and
  the M30 Feishu source integration. PraxisBase reimplements these behaviors in
  its own TypeScript and governance model; no Go source is copied.

- Open Knowledge Format (OKF) v0.1 (Apache-2.0, from
  GoogleCloudPlatform/knowledge-catalog). OKF is a vendor-neutral format for
  representing knowledge as plain markdown files with YAML frontmatter.
  PraxisBase's kb/ directory already embodies most OKF principles (markdown +
  frontmatter, required `type`, directory tree, git versioning, markdown links
  as relationships). Borrowed the `description` frontmatter field (consumed by
  the site graph tooltip, stable-knowledge list, and search index) and the
  progressive-disclosure concept. Format-idea reference only; no code copied and
  PraxisBase does not formally declare OKF compliance (the standard is v0.1
  Draft).

